text.section:
In determining if a conviction directly relates to the position of public employment sought or the occupation for which the license is sought, the hiring or licensing authority shall consider:
The nature and seriousness of the crime for which the individual was convicted;
The relationship of the crime to the purposes of regulating the position of public employment sought or the occupation for which the license is sought;
The relationship of the crime to the ability, capacity, and fitness required to perform the duties and discharge the responsibilities of the position of employment or occupation.
